Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper uses natural language processing techniques to analyze news articles related to infectious disease outbreaks. 
2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper analyzes the trends of news articles related to infectious disease outbreaks, which can be considered as a form of social network analysis. 
3. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper uses supervised temporal topic models to extract temporal topic trends from large corpora of news articles, which can be considered as an information retrieval task. 
4. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper describes a new approach for analyzing news trends related to infectious disease outbreaks, which can be considered as a software engineering task. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses time-series regression techniques to estimate disease case counts, which can be considered as a machine learning task.
